violent /ˈvaɪələnt/

1. ADJ If someone is violent , or if they do something that is violent , they use physical force or weapons to hurt, injure, or kill other people. 暴力的 

例： A quarter of current inmates have committed violent crimes. 四分之一的在押囚犯实施过暴力犯罪。 

例： ...violent anti-government demonstrations. …反政府的暴力示威。 

2. violently ADV 暴力地 [ADV with v] 

例： Some opposition activists have been violently attacked. 一些反对派激进分子遭到了暴力袭击。 

3. ADJ A violent event happens suddenly and with great force. 猛烈的 

例： A violent impact hurtled her forward. 一股剧烈的冲击力将她猛地向前抛了出去。 

4. violently ADV 剧烈地 [ADV with v] 

例： A nearby volcano erupted violently, sending out a hail of molten rock and boiling mud. 一座附近的火山猛烈爆发，喷出大量熔岩和沸腾的泥浆。 

5. ADJ If you describe something as violent , you mean that it is said, done, or felt very strongly. 强烈的 

例： Violent opposition to the plan continues. 对该计划的强烈反对在持续。 

例： He had violent stomach pains. 他有过剧烈的胃痛。 

6. violently ADV 强烈地 

例： He was violently scolded. 他受到了严厉叱责。 

7. ADJ A violent death is painful and unexpected, usually because the person who dies has been murdered. 暴力引起的 

例： ...an innocent man who had met a violent death. …一名遭暴力致死的无辜男子。 

8. violently ADV 谋杀性地 [ADV with v] 

例： ...a girl who had died violently nine years earlier. …9年前暴亡的一个女孩。 

9. ADJ A violent movie or television programme contains a lot of scenes that show violence. 多暴力场景的 (电影或电视节目) 

例： It was the most violent movie that I have ever seen. 这是我看过的最暴力的电影。

